description: From Middle English fyschehous, from Old English fisċhūs; equivalent to fish +‎ house.

entries.meaning: A business located at the water's edge that provides support to fishermen and which buys and then processes and onsells their catch.
A temporary shelter belonging to an individual fisherman for use while ice fishing.
A restaurant that specializes in fish and seafood.
A business that breeds fish for aquariums, selling them either to pet shops or directly to the public.
